50|$|The Type 45 240 mm {{howitzer}} (Yongo-shiki Nijyūyon-senchi Ryūdanhō) was a siege gun {{used by the}} Imperial Japanese Army during World War I and World War II. The Type 45 designation {{was given}} to this gun as it was accepted in the 45th year of Emperor Meiji's reign (1912). It was the first <b>such</b> <b>weapon</b> to be entirely designed in Japan.|$|R
